<dl id="n05013m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05013m">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05013m"> 13(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &mdash; chloroformed</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It would seem that <mark>Adam</mark> was expected to find a suitable partner. But nothing struck his fancy. Then the Lord put him into a deep sleep, carved out one of his ribs, and made it into a woman. It was the first surgical operation <mark>under chloroform</mark>. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Creation Story] 24</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
